                           --AMIGADOS GUIDE V2.6--
                                    BRU


   USE:
   BRU is a powerful Hard disk backup and restore utility included with
   AmigaDOS.

   PATH:
   Tools

   SYSTEM:
   2.0, 2.1, 3.0

   EXAMPLES:
   1>Stack 5000 (A large stack size is essential)
   1>CD DH0:
   1>BRU - (Select one of the options below and insert here).

   NOTES:
   In the example above DH0 is the source which will be backed-up.
   To select another source simply change the directory.

   Options:-
         C - Create a new archive.
         D - Check for differences between files already in archive.
         E - Estimate the number of disks required to create an archive.
         G - Only give information from the archive loader.
         H - Print help information for BRU.
         I - Check the specified archive for errors etc.
         T - List files stored in archive.
         X - Extract files from archive.

   There is no need to start with preformatted disks as BRU formats each
   disk as it goes.
